name: Clear
Start
Pause
Continue
Stop
Modbus
info:
Modbus controls for Dobot, only able to perform start pause continue and stop
Clear is used to clear the modbus, acts as a reset and should be used in the case modbus is not behaving properly. Genereally this feature should not be needed, only there as a precaution
More development can be done on this interface to be able to perform more features using modbus protocol to control the dobot
Work is referenced from Pei Wen, link to author source is https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1ZBdMco311Eqbl22KKzHNjs4gaVytvuDl

name: Jog with Joints/Cartesian
info: Allows user to jog the dobot in cartesian or joint angles by sending MQTT data to the python script

name: Run Python App with Jog & teach point functions
info:
Upon clicking this button, the node will run the python code necessary to control the dobot with
Change the filepath of the code inside the pythonshell in node
Also sends data to initalize the dobot to unlock robot joints
Note the format of typing the filepath in the pythonshell in node, example can be seen in the node

name: Stop App running
info: Terminate button sends string via MQTT to python script to stop the app

name: Choose Jog Mode
info: Allows user to choose the jog mode either in cartesian or joint angles as well as update the UI to reflect the selection

name: Get Angle and Pose data
info: This will receive angle and pose data from MQTT and format it to print into a table node

func:
path = global.get("path")
send = ""
fullpath = send.concat("\"",path,"\"")
msg.payload = fullpath
return msg;

name: Run Python File
info:
Enter the filepath of a python code to run, and the app will run it. This is meant to work in conjunction with the blockly python app.
This function is unable to loop code indefinitely, it will only run the script once.

func:
msg.payload = ""
return msg;

name: Save Teach Points
info:
This flow allows the user to save the current live angle and pose data which was obtained from the get live angle and pose data flow. 

The user may delete the teach points, cover the points and make the dobot move the exact teach point by holding down the run to button. 

The content in the table can be cleared by clicking the RESET button. 

The saved points are stored as an array of objects. Each object being a teach point with coordinate data.

name: MoveTo
Lock/unlock joints + clear error
info: Allow users to lock or unlock the joints via the enable robot button as well as clear errors that show up

name: Break
info: All this does is send MQTT data to topic/Break to break the code. It isn't really necessary

name: Move to the Teach Point
info:
When the run to button is held down, a message is sent to the Python script through MQTT to enable the robot to move to the teach point.

When the button is no longer held down, a new message is sent to the python script to stop the robot motion the teach point.
